ONGC Studies Buying Bashneft Stake With Group, Bashneft Says

-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 
2011-06-16T13:45:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-16/ongc-studies-buying-bashneft-stake-with-group-bashneft-says-1-.html
Oil and Natural Gas Corp.,  India ’s
largest state-owned energy explorer, is considering buying 25
percent of Russian oil producer OAO Bashneft with a group of
companies, according to Bashneft Chairman Alexander Goncharuk.  The companies, all from India, would purchase the stake
from Moscow-based AFK Sistema, Goncharuk said today at the St.
Petersburg Economic Forum.  Joeman Thomas, managing director of New Delhi-based ONGC
Videsh, ONGC’s overseas investment unit, declined to comment
when reached on his mobile phone today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amanda Jordan at 
 ajordan11@bloomberg.net  